Cody picked up his dart thoughtfully. The collision with the stone staircase did not seem to have damaged it at all. "One
more reason to love magic weapons," he said, sliding the dart back into its place alongside its fellows. He noticed Lulu
investigating the leash, sniffing it closely, and took another look at it himself. "I wonder..." he said. "The question, I
suppose, is whether keeping Lulu close is more or less conducive to good health than the alternative."
